					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10013569#post-4229004</guid>
				<title>Re: Author Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10013569/scp-4739#post-4229004</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 24 Apr 2019 22:08:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rigen</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2826105</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The name and the number is inherently connected tho. 4739 is GREY in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E.161">ITU-T E.161 standard keypad</a> that the main character's phone have, and this information is pivot to the storyline. Changing the number in the tale would make zero sense.</p> <p>IMO just let the two article be. It's not the first article that features SCP that's totally different with the actual article in the slot. And &quot;there's no canon&quot; basically guarantees it won't be the last</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10013569#post-4228946</guid>
				<title>Re: Author Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10013569/scp-4739#post-4228946</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 24 Apr 2019 20:46:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Cyberaven</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3986467</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I suppose if you didn't want to have Grey written up as a true SCP slot you could change the number used in the tale to be much higher, like a 7XXX or something like you did with several other mentioned SCPs in your stories. Alternatively, you could completely break the trend and put letters in the item number, SCP-4P39 or something, which would ensure the database never caught up with you trying to seperate stuff that doesn't need a real article.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
