					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10013569#post-4152740</guid>
				<title>Re: Author Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10013569/scp-4739#post-4152740</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 14 Feb 2019 00:54:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>qntm</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>571081</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Not a problem, thank you for filling this slot, it actually helps.</p> <p>For the benefit of everybody else reading this: in 2015, long before the SCP-4XXX series opened up, I wrote a Tale, <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/introductory-antimemetics">Introductory Antimemetics</a>, which featured an SCP named &quot;Alastair Grey&quot; with the number SCP-4739. When the SCP-4XXX series opened up, several people tried to write Grey up as a &quot;true&quot; SCP, but did not meet with success. Now I hope we may be past this. (In my opinion, Grey doesn't need a writeup, the Tale is sufficient by itself, and more effective.)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
